                    <span>First of all i want to start off saying that i'm a big Mase fan. I've been with him since the first day i heard his smoove rapping style and i am still with him until today. I personally have NOT read the book YET, but after reading the reviews and being down with mase for so long, you can be sure i am getting it ASAP, please belive that!! I myself am a lost christian, i have been caught up in this rap system and i'm trying to find a way out. And i truly believe that this book will help me find my way..back to God. Only he knows how much i need him in my life. I've been trying to get back on the right path, but I was afraid to lose my &#34;coolness&#34; and afraid of what my friends might think of me. But all that doesn't matter anymore. I will get there step by step and i'm only asking God to bare with me. 
<br />
<br />&#60; Back to Mase &#62;.... Many people out there would think that one must be crazy to give up their fortune, fame and luxurious life to follow something that doesn't directly give them the materialistic things. But i believe in Mase and I strongly belive that he was created for this! I remember on reading an interview where you were asked &#34; If you could give somethings away, what would it be?&#34;  his reponse was &#34; Everything...because i have God in my life and through him i can get it all back&#34;
<br />
<br />Bottom line is i'm really excited to this book and find more about this dude we call Mase aka Mason Betha and the messages he has for not only for the hip-hop community but for the whole world.
<br />
<br />-- GO BUY HIS &#34;WELCOME BACK&#34; If you don't have it yet, I belive it's a continuation of the book, with beautiful songs. GO GET!!</span>
                  
